      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-r&#34; data-lang=&#34;r&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(knitr) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;#include_graphics()&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(equatiomatic) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# extract_eq()&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(psych) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;#describe()&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(gtsummary) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;#tbl_summary()&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(summarytools) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;#descr()&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(stargazer) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;#stargazer()&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(sjPlot) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;#tab_model()&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(interactions) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;#interact_plot(), sim_slopes()&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(jtools) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;#summ()&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(tidyverse)&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;moderation&#34;&gt;Moderation&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#moderation&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;When the research hypotheses state that different categories, or levels of another variable, may have differing responses to other independent variables, we need to use interaction terms&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;- Also called &lt;strong&gt;moderation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;images/moderation.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: The relationship between &lt;em&gt;discrimination&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;grades&lt;/em&gt; depends on prog.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Graph drawn using &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;draw.io&#34;&gt;draw.io&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;moderation-example&#34;&gt;Moderation Example&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#moderation-example&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;anchor-symbol&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; height=&#34;26&#34; width=&#34;26&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 22 22&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;path d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&#xA;      &lt;path d=&#34;M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76.0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71.0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71.0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76.0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Suppose you are doing a simple study on weight loss and notice that people who spend more time exercising lose more weight.&#xA;Upon further analysis you notice that those who spend the same amount of time exercising lose more weight if they are more effortful.&#xA;The more effort people put into their workouts, the less time they need to spend exercising.&#xA;This is popular in workouts like high intensity interval training (HIIT).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
